bridge/ports
set interface pvid = access vlan

bridge/vlan
vlanid = 10
tagged = trunk ports, and bridge
untagged = untagged port

separate vlan for each tagged untagged

interfaces
add vlan-type interface, vlanid = 10, interface = bridge manage vlans 
repeat for each vlanid

ip/address
add new address, bind to interface/vlan above

VL192	192.168.1.0/24
VL10	10.0.0.0/16
VL172	172.16.1.0/30

create bridge br0
add ports 1-6,13-18 to bridge br0 (secure)
add ports 7,8 to bridge br0 (mgmt)
add ports 21,22 to bridge br0 (normal)
add ports 23,24 to bridge br0 (trunk)

set secure ports pvid = 10
set mgmt ports pvid = 99
set normal ports pvid = 20

bridge/vlan
create bridge/vlan for br0
1.	tagged		br0, ether23, ether24
	untagged	ether1-6, ether13-18
	vlanids		10
2.	tagged		br0, ether23, ether24
	untagged	ether7, ether8
	vlanids		172
3.	tagged		br0, ether23, ether24
	untagged	ether21, ether22
	vlanids		192

interface/
add new interface/vlan bind to interface bridge br0
address/
add new address to vlan interface
iv172	172.16.1.1/28	br0
iv192	192.168.1.253	ether23/24











